Section section_01 (Chars 0–7854):
Section Summary: The narrator's career as a writer is given a boost when his friend George Corvick asks him to review Hugh Vereker's new novel for "The Middle" magazine. Corvick is unable to write the review himself due to a personal emergency and entrusts the narrator with the task, urging him to truly understand Vereker's work. The narrator writes the review, but later feels uncertain about its quality, especially after Corvick expresses disappointment with it. The narrator meets Vereker at a social gathering, but doesn't get a chance to discuss the review with him, although Lady Jane's praise of the review in front of Vereker provides some vindication. The narrator is left with a desire to truly comprehend Vereker's work and prove himself as a capable critic.
